AB  - Skin disease ID with AI faces many tough parts. This list has things like unbalanced data, hard-to-get tech, gaps in how to see the AI's work, & use issues in actual clinics. This work brings up a new Mix Hybrid CNN-VIT model that also has Multi-Mode Clear AI (XAI). This mixed setup joins CNN's skill in close feature pulls with VT's wide area learning. This means better right hits & strong use. A shared learning setup lets many health places train the model. It does not need to share raw info. So, it keeps stuff private but makes the data set more mixed. Also, fake data made by GANs cuts bias in skin tones & disease steps not much seen. To make the AI work easier to get, the system uses multi-mode XAI. It gives both focus maps & words that match how skin docs think. Tuned for use at the edge, the model is ready for real-time use in clinics with few tools. Tests show it does better than old CNNs. It's righter & easier to see its work. This makes this way a big, fair & doc-friendly AI setup for skin checks.
