AB  - Manual document verification in recruitment incurs high costs, averaging 50 dollars per hour per reviewer with 15 percent error rates. The IDoc system, an Intelligent Document Processing framework, leverages fine-tuned Large Language Models such as LayoutLMv3, DONUT, and LiLT to achieve 95 percent text extraction accuracy and reduce demographic biases by 60 percent compared to untuned LLMs. This novel integration of adversarial debiasing and reinforcement learning in a multilingual IDP framework addresses gaps in existing systems. Evaluated on RVL-CDIP, XFUND, PubTables-1M, and a custom dataset, IDoc reduces processing time by 40 percent while ensuring GDPR and DPDP compliance through AES-256 encryption. Its optimization objective balances accuracy, fairness, and efficiency, making it a robust solution for recruitment automation. Beyond recruitment, IDoc's applications span finance, healthcare, and education, with future enhancements targeting handwritten text recognition and additional languages. This work advances equitable AI-driven document analysis, offering a scalable, fair, and efficient framework for intelligent document processing in diverse domains.
