AB  - The use of artificial intelligence in modeling and simulation is leading a technological revolution. This technology can efficiently capture the nonlinear characteristics and dynamic characteristics of complex systems, mine rules from historical data through machine learning algorithms, optimize model parameters, and construct high-precision mathematical models. In terms of simulation, artificial intelligence automatically generates realistic 3D scenes,automatically optimizes simulation parameters, and uses reinforcement learning technology to simulate human behavior, which improves the realism and reliability of simulation. In addition, AI enhances the realism of the simulated environment, simulates the human decision-making process, and provides powerful tools for optimizing design, model validation, and more. However, AI modeling and simulation still face challenges such as data requirements, interpretability, computational efficiency, and ethics. In the future, with the popularization of deep learning, reinforcement learning and other technologies, as well as the emergence of new models such as multimodal fusion and human-machine collaboration, artificial intelligence modeling and simulation technology will become more intelligent and efficient, and show broader application prospects in intelligent manufacturing, intelligent transportation, medical and health care,etc.
