T3  - AICI '25
AB  - Reliable medical diagnosis using MRI images with motion artifacts is rather challenging. Recently, many deep learning approaches have been proposed to reduce motion artifacts in MRI. However, these methods perform well on simulated motion artifacts but show limited effectiveness in removing real motion artifacts. To this, we propose a two-stage method that can significantly remove the real motion artifacts. We first train a de-motion network using a large dataset with simulated motion artifacts; the de-motion network can remove a part of the real motion artifacts. We then utilize the de-motioned output to guide the reverse generation process of the Diffusion model, generating more realistic images. Experimental results demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method on both simulated motion artifact data and real motion artifact data.
