TI  - EDPP-GAN: Synthesizing Tabular Data with Enhanced Dual Conditional Discriminators and Proximal-Pessimistic Nets
AU  - Wang, Gongju
AU  - Li, Yang
AU  - Yan, Long
AU  - Juxihong, Julaiti
AU  - Li, Dazhong
AU  - Zhang, Yinjun
AU  - Song, Yulun
T3  - ICCIP '24
AB  - As the application of machine learning expands, there is a corresponding escalation in the requirement for high-quality training data. However, obtaining large volumes of high-quality real data often faces challenges due to costs and privacy concerns. Recently, the emergence of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and other data generation technologies has paved the way for creating high-quality synthetic data. One of the challenge for such technologies is ensuring synthetic data retains similar utility as real data while adhering to privacy constraints. To overcome this, we propose the Enhanced Dual Conditional Discriminators and Proximal-Pessimistic Generative Adversarial Nets (EDPP-GAN) for tabular data generation. It incorporates gradient penalties, a novel PO loss, and dual conditional discriminators to enhance performance of conditional discriminators. Furthermore, by introducing pessimistic inputs to the conditional discriminators, the judgment of generator outputs becomes more stringent, thereby increase the effectiveness. Evaluations on four datasets show that EDPP-GAN closely mirrors real data in terms of machine learning utility. Moreover, the generated synthetic data meets similarity standards (Jensen-Shannon Divergence, Wasserstein Distance, Pair-wise Correlation) and is monitored using DCR and NNDR metrics to ensure compliance with privacy protection standards. Overall, experiments indicate that EDPP-GAN outperforms state-of-the-art tabular data generation algorithms.
